-- Singapore Airlines India joint venture gets flying permit
-- 
-- Mon Dec 15, 2014 08:51AM EST
-- None



MUMBAI, Dec 15 (Reuters) - Singapore Airlines Ltd's <SIAL.SI> Indian joint venture won a flying permit, paving way for it to start operations.

The joint venture with India's Tata conglomerate, which will operate under Vistara brand, plans to announce the sales, routes and schedules soon, it said in a statement.